g.text: UML Diagram: Class Population in Context
- Move the mouse cursor over a name to see more information.
- Click on a name to go to the corresponding page.
- The arrows of the inheritance tree are

a.title: ― InstanceVariable: Use of a represented variable within a data set.
a.xlink:title: ― InstanceVariable: Use of a represented variable within a data set.

a.title: ― Unit: Individual object of interest for some statistical activity, such as data collection.
a.xlink:title: ― Unit: Individual object of interest for some statistical activity, such as data collection.

a.title: ― PhysicalRecordSegment: Description of each physical storage segment required to completely cover a physical record representing the logical record.
a.xlink:title: ― PhysicalRecordSegment: Description of each physical storage segment required to completely cover a physical record representing the logical record.

a.title: ― DateRange: Expresses a date/time range using a start date and end date (both with the structure of Date and supporting the use of ISO and non-ISO date structures). Use in all locations where a range of dates is required, i.e. validFor, embargoPeriod, collectionPeriod, etc.
a.xlink:title: ― DateRange: Expresses a date/time range using a start date and end date (both with the structure of Date and supporting the use of ISO and non-ISO date structures). Use in all locations where a range of dates is required, i.e. validFor, embargoPeriod, collectionPeriod, etc.

a.title: ― Concept: Unit of thought differentiated by characteristics (from the Generic Statistical Information Model version 1.2: https://statswiki.unece.org/display/clickablegsim/Concept).
a.xlink:title: ― Concept: Unit of thought differentiated by characteristics (from the Generic Statistical Information Model version 1.2: https://statswiki.unece.org/display/clickablegsim/Concept).

a.title: ― CatalogDetails: A set of information useful for attribution, data discovery, and access.
a.xlink:title: ― CatalogDetails: A set of information useful for attribution, data discovery, and access.

a.title: ― InternationalString: Packaging structure for multiple language versions of the same string content. Where an element of this type is repeatable, the expectation is that each repetition contains different content, each of which can be expressed in multiple languages. The language designation goes on the individual String ...
a.xlink:title: ― InternationalString: Packaging structure for multiple language versions of the same string content. Where an element of this type is repeatable, the expectation is that each repetition contains different content, each of which can be expressed in multiple languages. The language designation goes on the individual String ...

a.title: ― LabelForDisplay: A structured display label. Label provides display content of a fully human readable display for the identification of the object.
a.xlink:title: ― LabelForDisplay: A structured display label. Label provides display content of a fully human readable display for the identification of the object.

a.title: ― Reference: Provides a way of pointing to resources outside of the information described in the set of DDI-CDI metadata.
a.xlink:title: ― Reference: Provides a way of pointing to resources outside of the information described in the set of DDI-CDI metadata.

a.title: ― Identifier: Identifier for objects requiring short- or long-lasting referencing and management.
a.xlink:title: ― Identifier: Identifier for objects requiring short- or long-lasting referencing and management.

a.title: ― ObjectName: A standard means of expressing a name for a class object. A linguistic signifier. Human understandable name (word, phrase, or mnemonic) that reflects the ISO/IEC 11179-5 naming principles.
a.xlink:title: ― ObjectName: A standard means of expressing a name for a class object. A linguistic signifier. Human understandable name (word, phrase, or mnemonic) that reflects the ISO/IEC 11179-5 naming principles.

a.title: ― InstanceKey: Single-valued key representation produced from the merge of the representations of all key members and a descriptor.
a.xlink:title: ― InstanceKey: Single-valued key representation produced from the merge of the representations of all key members and a descriptor.

a.title: ― DimensionalKeyDefinition: Collection of concepts that uniquely defines a collection of data points in a dimensional dataset.
a.xlink:title: ― DimensionalKeyDefinition: Collection of concepts that uniquely defines a collection of data points in a dimensional dataset.

a.title: ― Universe: Specialized unit type, with the specialization based upon characteristics other than time and geography.
a.xlink:title: ― Universe: Specialized unit type, with the specialization based upon characteristics other than time and geography.

a.title: ― InternationalString: Packaging structure for multiple language versions of the same string content. Where an element of this type is repeatable, the expectation is that each repetition contains different content, each of which can be expressed in multiple languages. The language designation goes on the individual String ...

a.title: ― ClassificationIndex: Ordered list of classification index entries.
a.xlink:title: ― ClassificationIndex: Ordered list of classification index entries.

a.title: ― ClassificationFamily: Collection of classification series related by being based on a common concept
a.xlink:title: ― ClassificationFamily: Collection of classification series related by being based on a common concept

a.title: ― DimensionalKey: Collection of data instances that uniquely identify a collection of data points in a dimensional dataset.
a.xlink:title: ― DimensionalKey: Collection of data instances that uniquely identify a collection of data points in a dimensional dataset.

a.title: ― AgentListing: Listing of agents of any type who may be organized to describe relationships between agents.
a.xlink:title: ― AgentListing: Listing of agents of any type who may be organized to describe relationships between agents.

a.title: ― measures: Set of specific units (people, entities, objects, events), usually in a given time and geography, being measured. Can be a specialization of the universe measured by a related represented variable.
a.xlink:title: ― measures: Set of specific units (people, entities, objects, events), usually in a given time and geography, being measured. Can be a specialization of the universe measured by a related represented variable.

a.title: ― represents: A record segment may represent a specific population or sub-population within a larger set of segments. Allows for the identification of this filter for membership in the segment.
a.xlink:title: ― represents: A record segment may represent a specific population or sub-population within a larger set of segments. Allows for the identification of this filter for membership in the segment.

a.title: ― isComposedOf: A unit in the population.
a.xlink:title: ― isComposedOf: A unit in the population.

a.title: ― narrows: Reference to a universe that the population narrows.
a.xlink:title: ― narrows: Reference to a universe that the population narrows.
